Our beautiful facility and 2020 Wing are ready for the return of our students beginning tomorrow for grades K-2. Our 3-6 grade students return on Wednesday.

Thank you to all who made this possible. We are very excited for the 2020-21 school year. While we face new challenges, we are overjoyed to welcome our students back for the first time since March. There is no better place to be than together.

Important: Parent Reopening Survey
As we begin to make plans for the reopening of schools, we would like to give you the opportunity to have input in our decision making process. We are required to submit a reopening plan to the state for approval by July 31st. Once approved, we will communicate the plan with you. We have been working with groups of individuals on our Reopening Committee Work Groups to help inform our plan. Please take a moment to answer the questions below. This survey will close on July 28th. As always, we appreciate your input and look forward to seeing you soon!
Follow this link to complete the survey:
https://forms.gle/j2mAehzrzGidTrv46

The East Quogue School District is seeking members for the Reopening Committee Work Groups. These groups will consist of administrators, teachers, staff, parents, community and Board of Education members. Each work group will report back to the Reopening Committee and make recommendations to the Superintendent of Schools. Our next meeting will be July 20th at 6:30pm. We will meet as a Reopening Committee then move to our work groups via breakout rooms. Please note, if you cannot be a part of these committees we will be seeking additional input via surveys that will be coming out soon.

Survey Link: https://forms.gle/39jjNvjYyGjgPReU8

Updated Information

Governor Cuomo, through an Executive Order signed yesterday, has officially changed the deadline for the submission of school budget ballots.

Effective immediately, the new deadline for the East Quogue School to receive ballots via mail is June 16. To submit your ballot in person at our drop box outside of the school, the deadline is June 9.

All ballots will be opened and final results will be tallied on June 16.

Thank you for your cooperation during these unique times. If you have any questions regarding the ballot process, please call us at 631-653-5210 or email at eqballot@eastquogue.k12.ny.us

post_text:
Reminder that our School Budget Vote will be held on Tuesday, June 9. Ballots are due by 5:00p.m. on that day. We have a drop box set up outside of the school every day for your convenience.

We are aware that some interior envelopes received by residents may have incorrect information for you to return to the Westhampton Beach School District. As long as you utilize the provided outer envelope addressed to the East Quogue School, that will suffice and ensure your ballot will be received.

If you have any questions regarding your ballot or are concerned you have not received a ballot, please contact us at eqballot@eastquogue.k12.ny.us . You may also call the school at 631-653-5210.

The Board of Education is committed to ensuring every registered voter in East Quogue has an opportunity to cast their vote.

A special thank you is extended to Mrs. Rezza and all of our volunteers who have worked so hard during this process.

May 28 at 12:00 PM ¬∑

You want to surprise me? You can't. I am unsurprisable (it's not a word but you get the point). I have a tendency to unknowingly figure out any surprise you have planned and spoil it. Or at least that was the case until yesterday.

Yesterday, Mr. Clemensen joined us on the Morning Music Show. 'Joined' isn't really the word, it was more of a 'take over'. He led our games (I cannot believe he doesn't know my least favorite fruit), and surprised me with a video from Michael Franti for my 33rd birthday. What? Where? When? How? Well done, Mr. Clemensen! Excellent surprise and I loved being able to share it with all of you!

Sharing the video here in case you missed it.

post_text:
Remember the Budget Vote June 9

Voting this year will be done completely via absentee ballot. Please make sure ballots are returned to the District by 5:00pm on June 9.

If you are registered in the District or through the Suffolk County Board of Elections, you are eligible to vote this year.

The East Quogue 2020-21 Draft School Budget is significantly under the Tax Cap, preserves and supports all of our wonderful programs for students and anticipates a tax rate asÔøº low as 8 years ago.

If you have any questions regarding the East Quogue School Budget, voter eligibility or any matter, please email Mr. Long at rlong@eastquogue.k12.ny.us

The Yankees lead the competition two weeks to one. Overall, the Mets have collected the most goods. This is an incredible job by all. The drive has supported hundreds of people. Let‚Äôs keep up the great work East Quogue.

Mrs. Clemensen's Music Page
April 20 at 1:15 PM ¬∑

I want to give a huge thank you to Mrs. Capozzola for joining us on The Morning Music Show with a new segment called ‚ÄòCooking with Cappy‚Äô! The students learned how to make a quick, easy, and fun dessert (recipe below as promised ‚ò∫Ô∏è) that they can make at home with their families. We loved having you and hope you can join us with another recipe again soon, Mrs. Capozzola! üíô

Funfetti-In-A-Mug Recipe:

Ingredients:
2 tbsp butter
2 tsp sugar
1/4 tsp vanilla
3 tbsp milk
4 tbsp flour
1/4 tsp baking powder
Sprinkles

Directions:
1. Place butter in a microwaveable mug. Microwave until melted (approx. 20 seconds).
2. Add in sugar, vanilla, milk, flour, baking powder, and sprinkles and mix throughout.
3. Microwave for 1 minute.
4. Enjoy!

1. Go to the woods. Bring a cone.üå≤üå≤üå≤
2. Put the cone in a pot - so that most of it stands out.
3. Pour it every day with a small amount of water, as excess water makes the cones rot.
4. After some time, a tiny tree will appear.
5. Congratulations - they just started oxygen production and you have a piece of forest in your own home.üçÅüçÇüçÉ.

You're doing something for nature, and you'll see what nature does for you..... üôåüôåüôå

Perfect project for the kids!!!

East Quogue School is offering Emergency Child Care to the children of first responders, medical service providers, transit workers and where space permits, other essential workers. This program will be held in Hampton Bays schools (or another selected location if you choose)

-Enrollment is on a first come first serve basis and enrollment may be limited based on space and/or staffing.

- Children must be school age Pre-K (must have turned 4 by 12/1/2019)-Grade 6.

-Program will be open Monday ‚Äì Friday. From 7:00 A.M. ‚Äì 6:30 P.M.

- Registration information is found on line at www.scopeonline.us. Click on the red button for Emergency Child Care. Children must be registered on line prior to attending.

Please see attached flyer for more information. Contact Dianna Gobler at (631) 504-7127 or dgobler@eastquogue.k12.ny.us

Can you guess who won our paper plane competition?
I challenge Mr. Schneider to a rematch! :)

A big thank you to Mr. Schneider (aka Schneiderbot) for coming on our show yesterday! We had a blast learning about how to create a perfect paper airplane!

If you liked Wednesday's shows, you're going to love what Mr. Schneider has coming your way!

On Fridays at 2:00pm, you'll have the opportunity to go on a virtual tour of the night sky, seeing that night's astronomical wonders. There will be fun activities that everyone can participate in!
Google Meet Code for Fridays:
https://meet.google.com/piu-xmra-sgv

On Mondays at 2:00pm, you'll "meet" up through Google Meet to make something fun! Each week, you will make something new, and share what you make!
Google Meet Code for Mondays:
https://meet.google.com/piu-xmra-sgv

You can receive any and all updates on what Mr. Schneider is up to on his Facebook page here:
facebook.com/eqsteam

And remember, you can tune in any Monday, Wednesday, and Friday to our Morning Music Talk Show via Google Meet at 10am! Can't wait to see you there!
